						<summary>

						<p>On the door-jamb at the entrance into the temple of Mallēśvarasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>RUDRADĒVA.</p>						

						<p>1271 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is dated in the Śaka year 1193, Prajāpati, Kārttīka. śu—</p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of two perpetual lamps to the temple of Bhōgēśvaradēva Mahādēva by Uttamagurudēva, son of Rājagurudēva. The engraver of the inscription is certain Appana Peggaḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
